Here's a PlantUML sequence diagram showing the deployment and data flow for the `fecgov_fec-eregs` system:

```plantuml
@startuml fecgov_fec-eregs

actor User
participant Frontend as "Frontend\n(Django Templates/JS)"
participant Backend as "Backend\n(Django Application)"
participant Database as "PostgreSQL\nDatabase"
participant ElasticSearch
participant CloudFoundry as "Cloud Foundry\n(cloud.gov)"
participant CMS as "External CMS"

== Deployment Phase ==
User -> CloudFoundry: Trigger deployment (CF push)
CloudFoundry -> Backend: Deploy application
CloudFoundry -> Database: Provision PostgreSQL service
CloudFoundry -> ElasticSearch: Provision ElasticSearch service
Backend -> Database: Run migrations
Backend -> ElasticSearch: Initialize indices

== Data Flow Phase ==
User -> Frontend: Access regulation page
Frontend -> Backend: GET /regulation/[section]
Backend -> Database: Query regulation data
Database --> Backend: Return MPTT structure
Backend -> ElasticSearch: Search supplements (if needed)
ElasticSearch --> Backend: Return search results
Backend --> Frontend: Render response

Frontend -> CMS: Fetch CMS content (async)
CMS --> Frontend: Return CMS data
Frontend -> Frontend: Combine data and render

User -> Frontend: Search regulations
Frontend -> Backend: POST /search {query}
Backend -> ElasticSearch: Full-text search
ElasticSearch --> Backend: Return results
Backend --> Frontend: Display results

== Data Update Flow ==
User -> Backend: Admin uploads new regulation
Backend -> Database: Store new version
Backend -> ElasticSearch: Update index
Backend -> Database: Calculate diffs (regcore_diff)

@enduml
```